items.itemDescription: Any equipment (tools, weapons or armour) that a zombie, skeleton, [more?] spawned with.
Amethyst is a crystal used for crafting and decoration.
Food item typically obtained from leaves
Arrows are consumed when firing with the bow.
Arrow variant dropped by stray
Baby chicken spawned from a thrown egg entity.
Dropped by breaking beetroot
Blaze rods are necessary progression items used to make blaze powder. They are also necessary in potions brewing
Crafting item made from bones.
Item dropped by skeleton variants. Used chiefly for crafting bone meal and taming wolves.
Edible vegetable. Obtained in this context as a random drop from zombie variants.
Teleports a short distance in a random direction when eaten. Dropped only by breaking a chorus plant, with a 50% chance.
Fuel and crafting item dropped by wither skeletons and coal ore.
items.adminNotes: ore source is not critical; ABNORMAL;

items.itemDescription: Raw cod is an uncooked food item dropped by guardians.
Copper ingots are used to craft various items
A decorative variant of the obsidian block.
Diamonds are one of the most iconic items in Minecraft. They are used for crafting tools, armour, weapons, and more
Dropped by vindicators or evokers.
Throwable item that teleports the player to its landing position, breaking on impact and imparting minor damage to the player.
Item used as keys to activate the ender portal frame; eyes of ender point towards strongholds when thrown.
Crafting item usually used for arrows.
Acts as a single-use flint: sets a targeted block on fire and vanishes on use.
Used to craft arrows and flint and steel.
Ghast tears can be used to brew potions.
Glow ink sacs can be used to customise signs.
Used as a crafting item, especially to make glowstone blocks; is also used in brewing.
A standard denomination of the metal gold. Used to craft gold items, blocks and nuggets.
Item dropped from mining gold ore; used to smelt into gold ingots.
Smallest denomination of gold metal. Used to craft items or gold ingots.
Gravel blocks fall, but are mostly only decorative. Can be used to make concrete powder.
Item used for crafting items and brewing potions.
Ink sacs can be made into black dye.
A standard denomination of the metal iron. Used to craft items, iron blocks and iron nuggets.
Smallest denomination of iron metal. Used to craft items or iron ingots.
Mineral used to craft blue dye and to enchant items in the enchanting table.
Crafting item obtained from certain animals.
Item dropped by magma cubes and used for brewing.
Melon slices are a type of food. Can also be made into glistering melon for use in brewing.
Melon seeds are used to plant melon crops.
Nether bricks are used to craft the nether brick decorative block.
Nether quartz is used to craft quartz decorative blocks.
Obsidan is a blast resistant building block, and is also used as a crafting item.
Phantom membranes are used to repair the elytra and in brewing.
Poisonous potatoes have no use.
Poppies are common red flowers.
Potatoes are a food item that can be made into baked potatoes in a furnace.
Potions of fire resistance make the entity affected immune to fire and lava damage.
items.adminNotes: Double chance to include splash potion

items.itemDescription: Prismarine crystals are a crafting item.
Prismarine shards are a crafting item.
Pufferfish is a poisonous food item that is used to brew water breathing potions.
Pumpkin seeds are used to plant the pumpkin crop.
A rabbit's foot can be used to brew potions.
Raw beef is a food item that can be cooked into steak.
Raw chicken is a food item that can be cooked into cooked chicken.
Raw copper can be smelted into copper ingots or used in crafting.
Raw copper can be smelted into iron ingots or used in crafting.
Raw mutton is a food item that can be cooked into cooked mutton.
Raw porkchops are food items that can be cooked into cooked porkchops.
Raw rabbits are food items that can be cooked into cooked rabbits.
Rotten flesh is a food item that induces the hunger status effect when eaten and cannot be cooked,
Raw salmon is a food item that can be cooked into cooked salmon.
Seagrass is an underwater plant used to feed turtles.
Shulker shells are used to craft shulker boxes.
Slimeballs are used for a wide variety of purposes.
Snowballs are used for crafting snow blocks and can be thrown.
Soul sand is a block that has a number of unique properties and uses.
Spider eyes are used to make fermented spider eyes, which are used for brewing.
String is a useful crafting item.
Sweet berries are a food item.
Tridents are a throwable weapon.
Tropical fish is a food item that cannot be cooked.
Wither skeleton skulls can be used to build the wither boss.
Wool is a block that can be used for decoration and crafting.
Blackstone is a block that can be used for decoration and crafting.
Spectral arrows apply the glow effect to targets hit by them.
Redstone dust is a unique item used for building circuitry and crafting machines.

sources.sourceText: Break Leaves
Kill any mobs that have spawned with equipment
Arrows can be obtained by killing a stray. They may drop 0 to 2 arrows with a uniform distribution. The graph depicts the probability that at least 1 will drop in your selected number of kills.
Arrow of slowness. This item behaves differently with looting.
Throwing an egg has a chance of spawning a baby chicken.
Breaking mature beetroot drops 1 to 4 beetroot seeds. If not mature, breaking yields only 1 beetroot seeds item.
Blazes may drop a blaze rod.
Killing cod, salmon, tropical fish or pufferfish yields 1 bone meal with a 5% chance.
The default skeleton or variants (wither skeleton, stray, and skeleton horse) drop 0-2 bones.
The default zombie or variants (zombie villager, husk, and chicken jockey) may drop carrots.
Fully mature carrot crops drop 2-5 carrots.
Breaking a chorus plant block will drop a chorus fruit 50% of the time.
Wither skeletons can drop a single coal.
Polar bears may drop 0-2 cod on death.
Dolphins may drop 1 cod on death
Guardians usually only drop cod with a 40% chance.
Elder guardians usually only drop cod with a 50% chance.
Drowned have a chance to drop copper ingots.
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Both vindicators and evokers may drop 0-1 emerald.
An ender pearl is a possible drop from killing an enderman.
An additional cod may be dropped with a 1.5% chance.
An additional cod may be dropped with a 1.5% chance.
A thrown eye of ender acts as an entity and upon the end of a use, has a chance to shatter or drop the item again.
Adult chickens drop 0-2 feathers on death.
Parrots drop 1-2 feathers on death.
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Breaking gravel has a chance to drop flint.
A single ghast tear may be dropped by ghasts.
Glow squids drop 1-3 glow ink sacs on death.
sources.adminNotes: Possibly not type 2. investigate similar items

sources.sourceText: Witches have a 12.5% chance to drop 0-6 glowstone; the 12.5% is divided equally between each number.
Mining glowstone yields 2-4 glowstone dust.
Zombified piglins have a 2.5% chance to drop a gold ingot.
Gold ore yields 1 raw gold without fortune.
Coal ore drops 1 coal when mined without fortune.
Zombified piglins may drop a gold nugget.
Gold ore variant found in the nether; drops 2-6 gold nuggets.
Type of block found in bastions; 10% chance to drop 2-5 gold nuggets with a uniform distribution, otherwise drops itself as a block.
Gravel block has a 90% chance of dropping on breaking a gravel block (since flint drops 10% of the time).
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Creepers drop 0-2 gunpowder.
Ghasts drop 0-2 gunpowder.
Witches have a 12.5% chance to drop 0-6 gunpowder; the 12.5% is divided equally between each number.
Squids drop 1-3 ink sacs on death.
The default zombie or variants (zombie villager, husk, and chicken jockey) may drop iron ingots with a 2.5% chance.
Iron golems drop 3-5 iron ingots on death. Looting does not apply.
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Lapis lazuli ore drops 4-9 lapis lazuli items.
Cows, hoglins, horses, donkeys, mules, and llamas each drop 0-2 leather
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Magma cubes drop 0-1 magma creams if they are larger than the smallest magma cube size.

Melon stems drop 0-3 melon seeds when broken.

Nether quartz ore drops 1 nether quartz  without fortune.

Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Phantoms may drop 1 phantom membrane on death.
Mature potato crops may drop 1 poisonous potato with a 2% chance.
Iron golems drop 0-2 poppy flowers upon dying.
Mature potato crops drop 1-4 potatoes when harvested.
The default zombie or variants (zombie villager, husk, and chicken jockey) may drop potatoes with a 2.5% chance.
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Guardians have a 40% chance of dropping a prismarine crystal on death.
Elder guardians have a 1/3 chance of dropping a prismarine crystal on death.
Sea lanterns drop 2-3 prismarine crystals on breaking.
Guardians and elder guardians have a 2/3 chance of dropping prismarine shards on death.
Guardians and elder guardians have a 0.325% chance of dropping a pufferfish on death.
Pumpkin stems drop 0-3 pumpkin seeds when broken.
Rabbits have a 10% chance to drop a rabbit's foot.
Cows and mooshrooms drop raw 1-3 raw beef on death (steak if died while on fire).
Chickens drop 1 raw chicken on death without fortune (cooked chicken if died while on fire).
Mining copper ore with a stone pickaxe or better drops 2-5 raw copper items.
Iiron ore drops 1 raw iron.
Sheep drop raw 1-2 raw mutton on death (cooked mutton if died while on fire).
Pigs drop raw 1-3 raw porkchops on death (cooked porkchops if died while on fire).
Hoglins drop raw 2-4 raw porkchops on death (cooked porkchops if died while on fire).
Rabbits drop 1 raw rabbit on death without fortune (cooked rabbit if died while on fire).
The default zombie or variants (zombie villager, husk, chicken jockey, drowned, and zombie horse) may drop 0-2 rotten flesh.
Zombified piglins may drop 1 rotten flesh on death.
Zoglins drop 1-3 rotten flesh on death.
Polar bears have a 1/6 chance of dropping at least 1 salmon.
Guardians and elder guardians have a 0.625% chance to drop a salmon.
Turtles drop 0-2 seagrass on death.
Shulker mobs may drop 1 shulker box on death.
The smallest naturally occurring slimes (size 1) drop 0-2 slime balls on death.
Baby pandas have a 1/700 chance of dropping a slimeball when sneezing.
Snow golems drop 0-15 snowballs on death, unaffected by looting.
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Spiders, spider jockeys, and cave spiders each may drop 1 spider eye on death.
Witches have a 12.5% chance to drop 0-6 spider eyes; the 12.5% is divided equally between each number.
Cats drop 0-2 string on death.
Striders drop 2-5 string on death.
Spiders, spider jockeys, and cave spiderseach drop 0-2 string items on death.

Fully mature sweet berry bushes drop 2-3 berries when broken
Sweet berry bushes in the last third of their maturity drop 1-2 sweet berries when broken.
There is an 8.5% chance of a drowned dropping a trident, if holding one. 6.25% of drowned spawn holding tridents.
Guardians and elder guardians have a 0.05% chance to drop a tropical fish.
Wither skeletons have a 2.5% chance to drop a wither skeleton skull.
Shearing a sheep drops 1-3 wool (killing only drops 1)
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Giving a piglin golden ingots yields various items.
Emerald ore drops 1 emerald without fortune.
Redstone ore drops 4-5 redstone dust.
